Description: ### AboutFrom the [about page](http://rosettaproject.org/about/):> The Rosetta Project is a global collaboration of language specialists and native speakers working to build a publicly accessible digital library of human languages. Since becoming a National Science Digital Library collection in 2004- the Rosetta Archive has more than doubled its collection size- now serving nearly 100-000 pages of material documenting over 2-500 languagesâ€”the largest resource of its kind on the Net.### Downloads  * [Rosetta Project collection at the Internet Archive](http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject)  * [Rosetta Project at Freebase](http://rosetta.freebase.com/)
